Maybe after a certain period if time one of his placeholders despawns and he spawns? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upeacefulsalvation.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peaceful Salvation</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/02 10:38:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9608.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vaniki</span><hr size=1> I assure you that it works like this:<br>
<br>
He can be a completely random spawn -OR- You can clear out some PH'er and he'll sometimes pop. <br>
<br>
The reason I say this, is because I've seen him spawn randomly when no chetari's have been killed. However, I've also been on a guild raid where we killed him, and he respawned literally 5 minutes after we killed him the first time...He is definitely not on a consistent timer. However, if you wait long enough, he may spawn on his own without killing PH'ers. <br>
<br>
More evidence that suggests this, is that there have been reports of people trying to drop an item, and accidently opening up a trade window with an invisible NPC called &quot;Vaniki_Placeholder00&quot;, or something to that effect.<br>
<br>
Your best bet is to do sweeps through the entire chetari side until he spawns. I know this to be true from experience.<br>
